RBS Plans $1.6 Billion Sale of Property Legacy Loans, FT Says

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-02-21T00:34:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/rbs-plans-1-6-billion-sale-of-property-legacy-loans-ft-says.html
  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc  is
preparing to sell $1.6 billion of unwanted loans left over from
when the commercial-property sector was booming, the Financial
Times reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the
matter.  The bank has asked private-equity groups including  Lone
Star Funds , Starwood Capital Group LLC and Blackstone Group LP
to sign a non-disclosure agreement as a start to the process,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in  London  at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 